{
  "texts": [
    "Typically, 75% of the data is used for training, 12.5% for validation, and 12.5% for testing.",
    "In a neural network classifier, the model is trained through multiple iterations (epochs) to adjust internal weights and minimize prediction errors.",
    "The training set optimizes these weights, while the validation set evaluates the model's performance on unseen data during each epoch.",
    "This configuration means the validation set is involved in training and guiding adjustments in subsequent epochs.",
    "Consequently, the test set, kept entirely separate from training, is used only after the model is fully trained to provide an unbiased evaluation of its generalization performance on new data."
  ]
}